Sentencas: Three-phase boundary length and gas diffusion characteristics significantly influence the performance of solid oxide electrolysis cell (SOEC) Supporting structure of gradient pores can not only increase the three-phase boundary length but also improve the gas diffusion characteristics which helps reducing the polarization impedance of SOEC and elevating electrolysis performance.
Titulo: A Support Structure with Gradient Pores Used for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: 8YSZ (8 mol % Yttria stabilised Zirconia power), the mature electrolyte material, and freeze casting process were used to prepare a supporting structure with gradient pores used for solid oxide electrolysis cell(SOEC).
Titulo: A Support Structure with Gradient Pores Used for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: Optimized conditions such as solid content, frozen temperature, dispersing agent and binder etc were investigated.
Titulo: A Support Structure with Gradient Pores Used for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscope (SEM) was applied to characterize microstructure of the support plate prepared.
Titulo: A Support Structure with Gradient Pores Used for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: The results indicate that the solid content is a determinant factor affecting plate intensity and pore size while the microstructure depends on frozen temperature.
Titulo: A Support Structure with Gradient Pores Used for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell
